    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Flyspeck, traditionally defined as a tiny stain created by insect excrement, is a painting process of feeding flies acyllic paint and sugar water, then allowing the flies to excrete onto a canvas.</Note_Text>
